<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-4187] GDK should make the File method  setText(String text, String charset)    an alias for   write(String text, String charset)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-4187</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Because GDK makes the File method setText(String text) an alias for  write(text),&lt;br/&gt;
and because it&apos;s possible to say both  getText()  and getText(String charset),&lt;br/&gt;
it feels clunky that there is no  setText(String text, String charset).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In short, the following is annoying:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;myfile.getText(charset)   
...
myfile.write(text,charset)     &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Hm... I wish   myfile.setText(text,charset) just worked here too.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems like adding this alias would not break anybody&apos;s code,&lt;br/&gt;
and would remove a silly-thing-you-gotta-remember.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
